<chapter xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"  xml:id="chap_null_space">
  <title>The Null Space and Column Space of a Matrix</title>
  <introduction>
    <objectives>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the null space of a matrix?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the column space of a matrix?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What important structure do the null space and column space of a matrix have?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the kernel of a matrix transformation?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How is the kernel of a matrix transformation <m>T</m> defined by
            <m>T(\vx) = A\vx</m> related to the null space of <m>A</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            What is the range of a matrix transformation?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How is the range of a matrix transformation <m>T</m> defined by
            <m>T(\vx) = A\vx</m> related to the column space of <m>A</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we find a basis for <m>\Nul A</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            How do we find a basis for <m>\Col A</m>?
          </p>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </objectives>
  </introduction>
